history.content:
Hi, 

I was wondering what the difficulty and workload of EECS 106B is (relative to CS upper div courses)? Also how important is it to have EECS 106A done before taking the course? 

Lastly, due to the short time I have left at Berkeley, if you strongly advise against taking EECS 106B without taking 106A, what are some courses you recommend me taking that would give me some the same skills? 

Thanks!
history.subject: EECS 106B (Robotic Manipulation and Interaction) Workload and Difficulty
